<dl id="n01082c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01082c">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01082c"> 82(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 14&frasl;xii halcyon / 28&frasl;xii (Kingfisher) days</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[SOME CHRISTMAS TRADITIONS / [&hellip;]</font> / The <mark>&ldquo;Halcyon&rdquo; Days</mark>. / (By F.P.C.)] The &ldquo;halcyon days,&rdquo; <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> were anciently the <mark>seven days preceeding and the seven days following December 21st</mark> <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Popular belief has it that by reason of the brooding of the <mark>&ldquo;halcyon bird,&rdquo; as the kingfisher is called</mark>, at this period the sea becomes calmy <small> <a name="IT23dec22" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IT23dec22"><cite title="source">Irish Times</cite></a> (23 December 1922) 7/1</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05144k" href="c05all.htm#c05144k">VI.C.05:144(k)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
